                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/197: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-13T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 13, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>205. <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName> resigned and delivered the
                    power to his Minister of the Interior, <persName corresp="#p_BEGB1">General
                        Blanche</persName>, who was provisional Vice President and who declares that
                    he will carry out the Socialist idea. It is apparently a victory for <persName
                        corresp="#p_MRR1">Merino</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
